size:
Oris Ocean Trilogy Set - a limited & numbered edition set of only 200 sets, with all 3 pieces sharing the same limited edition number. The trio of watches includes the: • Oris Blue Whale limited edition 200 pieces, available exclusively as part of the Oris Ocean Trilogy set).

• Oris Great Barrier Reef III limited edition 2000 pieces.

• Oris Clean Ocean limited edition 2000 pieces.

The set is delivered in an exclusive & eye-catching presentation box produced from used plastic bottles. Only chemically inert recycled plastic waste was selected as part of the process. The box is created in 4 steps: • Use plastic bottles are collected.

• The plastic bottles are then shredded into small pieces.

• The pieces are selectively hand arranged & then pressed into a panel. The hand selection & positioning of the various colored bottle makes each panel unique.

• Finally the panels are cut to size & assembled as the outer shell of the Oris Ocean Trilogy presentation box .

size:
The OMEGA Speedmaster is one of OMEGA’s most iconic timepieces. Having been a part of all six lunar missions, the legendary Speedmaster is an impressive representation of the brand’s adventurous pioneering spirit. This OMEGA Speedmaster Broad Arrow 1957 Chronograph features a brown dial graced by a small seconds sub-dial, 30-minute recorder and 12-hour recorder along with a central chronograph and “broad arrow” hour and minute hands, as well as a scratch-resistant sapphire crystal. There is a date window at the 6 o’clock position. The 18K red gold bezel, with its tachymetric scale, is mounted on a 42 mm stainless steel casebody and presented on a stainless steel bracelet. At the heart of this timepiece is the Co-Axial calibre 3313 which is visible through the transparent caseback.





New and unworn with all new accessories and our own 3 years warranty





Shipped by DHL, FedEx, or Japan Post EMS (*import duty and tax/VAT charged additionally if necessary)





FEATURES: Chronograph, Chronometer, Date, Small seconds, Tachymeter, Transparent case back


Total product weight (approx.): 179 g


Between lugs: 20 mm


Case: Steel ‑ red gold


Case diameter: 42 mm


Water resistance: 10 bar (100 metres / 330 feet)


Calibre: OMEGA 3313


Self‑winding chronograph movement with column wheel mechanism and Co‑Axial escapement. Free sprung balance, with date, hour, minute and continuous small seconds hands, central chronograph hand.


Power reserve: 52 hours


Type: Self winding
